sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User (browser / app)
    participant IDP as Platform IdP<br/>(OIDC)
    participant AS as AppSync GraphQL
    participant DDB as DynamoDB<br/>(InboxItem · DeviceToken)
    participant P as Producer service
    participant IN as Intake λ
    participant TOPIC as SNS topic
    participant IQ as inbox-q
    participant IW as Inbox λ

    Note over U,IDP: ① LOGIN — establish identity
    U->>IDP: authenticate (SSO)
    IDP-->>U: JWT { tenantId, userId, roles }
    Note over U: every CNS call now carries this JWT — keys are derived from it server-side

    Note over U,DDB: ② OPEN THE NOTIFICATION CENTER
    U->>AS: registerDevice {platform, token}  (for push)
    AS->>DDB: PutItem DeviceToken (tenant#user)
    U->>AS: query inbox(cursor) + unreadCount
    AS->>DDB: Query PK=tenant#user (visibility filter) — direct JS resolver, no Lambda
    DDB-->>AS: page of items + counter
    AS-->>U: {items, unreadCount}
    U->>AS: subscription onInboxEvent(me)
    Note over AS: subscription auth pins userId = JWT identity —<br/>AppSync now holds the live connection (nothing for CNS to manage)

    Note over P,IW: ③ A NOTIFICATION IS PRODUCED (while the user is online)
    P->>IN: POST /v1/notifications {eventId, typeId, recipient=this user}
    IN->>DDB: idempotency put · payload→payloadRef
    IN->>TOPIC: publish · attrs channels=[inApp] · stage=deliver
    IN-->>P: 202 accepted
    TOPIC->>IQ: filter channels ∋ inApp
    IQ->>IW: receive
    IW->>DDB: TransactWrite item (state=unread) + unread_ctr +1
    IW->>AS: publishInboxEvent (IAM mutation)

    Note over U,AS: ④ THE USER SEES IT — live, no refresh
    AS-->>U: onInboxEvent {kind: UPSERT, item} + {kind: BADGE, unread}
    Note over U: Bell increments and the row appears — p99 ≤ 1.5 s from POST.<br/>Had the user been offline, the same item is read from the store on next inbox query (socket is only an optimization).
